\pard\sb240\sa60\b\f0\fs36 Lyrion Music Server Driver v2.0\b0\fs22\par

\pard\sb200\sa60\b\fs28 Overview\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fs22 This driver enables RTI control systems to control Lyrion Music Server (LMS, formerly Logitech Media Server / Squeezebox Server) and its connected players. Up to 20 players can be controlled with a single driver instance. All players must connect to the same LMS server.\par
\pard\sb60\fs22 The driver communicates with LMS using the CometD/Slim API over TCP (default port 9000). It maintains a persistent connection and subscribes to real-time player status updates.\par

\pard\sb240\sa60\b\fs28 Requirements\b0\fs22\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Lyrion Music Server running on the local network\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab One or more Lyrion/Squeezebox-compatible players (hardware Squeezebox devices or software players such as Squeezelite)\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab RTI processor with a Two-Way IP connection slot available\par

\pard\sb240\sa60\b\fs28 Configuration Settings\b0\fs22\par

\pard\sb160\sa40\b\fs24 Default Server\b0\fs22\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Server Name\b0  (Defaul_Server_Name) \emdash  Friendly name, documentation only\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b TCP Address\b0  (Defaul_Server_IP) \emdash  IP address of the LMS server\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b TCP Port\b0  (Default_Server_TCP_Port) \emdash  LMS port, default 9000\par

\pard\sb160\sa40\b\fs24 Player Settings (P01\endash P20)\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fs22 Player settings are shown per-player based on the Total Players setting. Player numbers are zero-padded (P01, P02, etc.).\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\sb60\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Player Name\b0  (NameP##) \emdash  Must exactly match the player name as it appears in LMS. The driver discovers players from the server and matches them by name.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Use Custom Parent Menu\b0  (Use_Custom_Parent_Menu_P##) \emdash  Enable custom home menu ordering and renaming.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Custom Parent Menu Order\b0  (Custom_Menu_Order_P##) \emdash  Colon-separated list of internal menu item names to display (see Custom Parent Menu section).\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Custom Parent Menu Names\b0  (Custom_Menu_Names_P##) \emdash  Colon-separated display names shown on the remote. Must contain the same number of items as the Order field.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Skip First Pandora Menu\b0  (SkipFirstPandoraMenuP##) \emdash  Jump directly to the Pandora Stations list, bypassing the Pandora top-level menu.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Hide MySqueezebox.com\b0  (Favorites_Hide_MySqueeze_P##) \emdash  Hide the MySqueezebox.com entry from the Favorites menu.\par

\pard\sb160\sa40\b\fs24 Remote Control Settings (Advanced)\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fs22 Optionally assign page-navigation macros per remote so the driver can redirect to the browse list or keyboard page during interaction.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\sb60\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Total Remotes\b0  (TotalRemotes) \emdash  Number of remotes with custom macro assignments.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Remote Control Name\b0  (NameR#) \emdash  The view name of the remote as it appears in Integration Designer.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Keyboard Page Macro\b0  (KeyboardPageMR#) \emdash  Macro to navigate to the keyboard page when search input is required.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Browse Page Macro\b0  (BrowsePageMR#) \emdash  Macro to navigate to the browse list page.\par

\pard\sb160\sa40\b\fs24 Debug Settings\b0\fs22\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab \b Enable Trace\b0  (DebugTrace) \emdash  Enable verbose debug output. View with RTI Diagnostic Driver.\par

\pard\sb240\sa60\b\fs28 Custom Parent Menu\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fs22 The driver retrieves the home menu from LMS and displays it as a browse list. By default it shows all items in the order provided by LMS. To control the order or rename items, enable \b Use Custom Parent Menu\b0  and configure both \b Custom Parent Menu Order\b0  and \b Custom Parent Menu Names\b0 .\par
\pard\sb60\fs22 Both fields must contain an equal number of colon-separated items. The Order field contains the exact internal menu names returned by LMS; the Names field contains the display names shown to the user.\par
\pard\sb60\fs22 To discover internal menu names: enable \b Enable Trace\b0 , load the driver, then call the \b Print Home Menu Items to Log File\b0  function from Integration Designer. The trace log will output a colon-separated list of available home menu names.\par
\pard\sb60\fs22 Example:\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs20 Custom Parent Menu Order: Favorites:Pandora:Spotify:radios:Artists:Genres\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs20 Custom Parent Menu Names: Favorites:Pandora:Spotify:Radio:Artists:Genres\par
\pard\f0\fs22\par

