\pard\sb240\sa60\b\fs28 Notes & Behaviors\b0\fs22\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Player names must exactly match what appears in the LMS web interface. The driver performs a server status request on startup and matches configured players by name.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab The driver uses a single TCP connection per server. All players on the same server share the connection.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab The browse list loads 25 items per request. The Now Playing queue paginates similarly and is rebuilt from scratch whenever LMS reports a changed playlist timestamp.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Sync slave players inherit now-playing metadata (title, artist, album, cover art, progress, etc.) from the sync master. Volume is maintained independently per player.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Pandora Thumbs Down does not immediately skip the track; LMS will advance to the next track after reporting the ban.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Play a Random Playlist searches the Favorites list (optionally scoped to a named subfolder) for playlist-type entries and plays one at random.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360\fs22 \bullet\tab Save Default Station / Play Default Station use driver Persistence storage keyed by player MAC address.\par

\pard\sb240\sa60\b\fs28 Revision History\b0\fs22\par
\pard\li720\fs22 \b 2.0\b0\tab Complete TypeScript rewrite using the RTI SDK package ecosystem. Replaced the legacy monolithic JS file with a modular class-based architecture (Server, Player, RemotePlayer). Improved HTTP chunked-transfer decoding, paginated queue handling, per-remote browse list state isolation with correlation IDs, and structured logging.\par
\pard\li720\fs22 \b .94\b0\tab Added multi-instance support and auto-tagging.\par
\pard\li720\fs22 \b .93\b0\tab Fixed history bug so the top of the list is set to the last selected item when browsing back up a level.\par
\pard\li720\fs22 \b .92\b0\tab Beta.\par
